God made Heaven and Earth. Maimonides and Manaſſeh Ben Iſrael obſerve theſe three words uſed in Scripture, when Creation of the world is attributed to God, viz.
〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉 ; and that 〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉 ſignifies the production of things out of nothing, which is the Schools Notion of Creation;
〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉 is the making up a thing perfect and compleat, according to its own kinde and properties;
〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉 intimates the dominion and right poſſeſſion that God has of all things thus created or made. But though 〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉 according to the mind of the Learned Jews, ſignifies Creation properly ſo called, yet the Seventy obſerve no ſuch Criticiſme, but tranſlate it 〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉 , which is no more then made. And vulgar men are not at leiſure to diſtinguiſh ſo ſubtilly. Wherefore this latter ſenſe I receive as the vulgar Literal ſenſe, the other as Philoſophical. And where I uſe the word Creation in this Literal Cabbala, I underſtand but that common and general Notion of Making a thing, be it with what circumſtances it will.

